[[File:Factoría de salazones 001.jpg|thumb|250px|Roman fish salting factory]]
The '''Roman fish salting factory''' ({{lang-es|Factoría romana de salazones}}) was a salting factory established on the seafront of [[Algeciras]], southeastern [[Spain]] by the Romans.<ref name="Pérez2008">{{cite book|last=Pérez|first=Emilio Menéndez|title=Las Rutas de la Sal|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dY3wUNk07s8C&pg=PA72|accessdate=18 February 2013|date=1 March 2008|publisher=Netbiblo|isbn=978-84-9745-096-6|page=72|language=Spanish}}</ref> It belonged to the fishing village of San Nicolás, part of what was called [[Caetaria]].<ref name="2. Congreso Internacional La Ciudad en al-Andalus y el Magreb">{{cite book|title=2. Congreso Internacional La Ciudad en al-Andalus y el Magreb|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4HjwCyXHkkoC&pg=PA297|accessdate=18 February 2013|year=2002|publisher=Fundación El legado andalusì|language=Spanish|isbn=978-84-932051-7-1|page=297}}</ref> A site of archaeological and historical interest, it was declared a [[Bien de Interés Cultural]] site on 27 June 2002. 

